---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="week 13 — three ben thompson pieces and one surprise" description="the stratechery streak continued. then a journalist built an iOS app with claude code and made me think harder than any of ben's frameworks.">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-4">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">reading</a> <span class="text-faint">/</span> week 13
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-normal animate-fade-up">three ben thompson pieces and one surprise</h1>

    <div class="essay mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <p>read four things this week</p>

      <p class="mt-6">three from the same person</p>
      <p class="text-dim">one from a journalist who learned to code</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the journalist hit harder</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>ben thompson on jensen huang and accelerated computing</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the "next industrial revolution" frame</p>

      <p class="mt-6">it's clean</p>
      <p>it's probably right</p>
      <p class="text-dim">it didn't change anything about what i'm building tomorrow</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://stratechery.com/2026/an-interview-with-jensen-huang-about-accelerated-computing" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">An Interview with Jensen Huang →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>ben on microsoft bundling claude into copilot</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the pricing floor for ai features just shifted</p>

      <p class="mt-6">when the biggest distributor commoditizes the model layer</p>
      <p class="text-gold">the value moves to what you do with it</p>

      <p class="mt-6">hot take doesn't compete on model</p>
      <p class="text-dim">it competes on context</p>
      <p>so this is tailwind not headwind</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://stratechery.com/2026/copilot-cowork-anthropics-integration-microsofts-new-bundle" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">Copilot Cowork, Anthropic's Integration →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>ben on winners losers and unknowns in 2026</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the structural landscape piece</p>

      <p class="mt-6">reads like a map</p>
      <p class="text-spice">maps are useful when you already know where you're going</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://stratechery.com/2026/2026-11-winners-losers-and-the-unknown" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">2026.11: Winners, Losers, and the Unknown →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>then the lenny piece</p>

      <p class="mt-6">a journalist learned ios development through claude code</p>

      <p class="mt-6">no engineering background</p>
      <p>no bootcamp</p>
      <p class="text-crimson">just a tool that made the gap crossable</p>

      <p class="mt-6">i've been building for years</p>
      <p>co-founded a marketplace</p>
      <p>shipped smart contracts</p>

      <p class="mt-6">and this person just</p>
      <p class="text-spice">skipped the queue</p>

      <p class="mt-6">not threatening</p>
      <p class="text-dim">clarifying</p>

      <p class="mt-6">if the tool flattens the building curve</p>
      <p>the edge isn't craft anymore</p>
      <p class="text-gold">it's knowing what to build</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://lennysnewsletter.com/p/from-journalist-to-ios-developer" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">From journalist to iOS developer →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>pattern this week</p>

      <p class="mt-6">ben gives you the map</p>
      <p>lenny gives you the mirror</p>

      <p class="mt-6">three frameworks and one story</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the story stayed with me longer</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">← back to reading</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .essay p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
